# Keyword Ability Engine Guide

- Keep runtime behavior in the engine pipeline: `decomposePlayerAction` -> `runChecks` -> `applyAtomicAction`.
- Implement keyword rules in engine helpers and atomic execution paths, not in UI/store components.
- Prefer reusable primitives in `utils` for movement/targeting legality, then call them from `applyAtomicAction`.
- Add deterministic error strings for illegal moves so orchestrator tests can assert exact outcomes.
- For movement keywords, model legality by location and region (`surface`, `underground`, `underwater`, `void`), not square-only assumptions.
- Treat `flooded` as a water-site condition when evaluating movement/location requirements.
- Keep `CheckAction` focused on preconditions and `MutationAction` focused on state transitions.
- Any keyword behavior change must add or update focused tests in `src/engine/tests/orchestrator.test.ts`.
